cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL

The paper deals with automata models for reasoning tasks on data trees, which are commonly used in databases and programming languages. The paper also discusses logical characterizations and complexity results for the automata models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with data values in trees, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases), and the use of automata models suggests that it could belong to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses unranked trees, which suggests that it could belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
